UID:13190-1772874000-1772884800@durhamcentralpark.org
SUMMARY:Durham Farmers' Market
DESCRIPTION:The Durham Farmers’ Market is a community of farmers\, growers and crafters. We are strongly committed to local products: every item you see at the market was produced by the people selling it\, and it all comes from no more than 70 miles away. \nThe Durham Farmers’ Market open Saturdays mornings for local produce\, flowers\, crafts and more! The Wednesday Market is open from 3-6pm Wednesdays\, Mid-April through Mid-October \nIf you’d like more information about this week’s vendor list\, SNAP benefits and map\, visit durhamfarmersmarket.com \n\nWe are happy to offer Double Bucks to our SNAP clients. This means is a SNAP client has $10\, they receive $20 in tokens to spend at the winter market.\n\nEstamos muy contentos de ofrecer Double Bucks a nuestros clientes de SNAP. Esto significa que si un cliente de SNAP gasta $ 10\, recibirá $ 20 en tokens para gastar en productos frescos.\n\n\nAdditionally\, we offer a cash match program for other qualifying folks. To receive this benefit\, simply bring cash to the info table. Then\, we’ll double the amount with tokens. For example\, $10 in cash equals $20 in tokens.\n\nTambién ofrecemos un programa de contrapartida en efectivo para nuestros beneficiarios de SNAP que no tienen beneficios durante el mes\, clientes de WIC y miembros de la comunidad que viven en viviendas públicas. Para recibir este beneficio\, simplemente traiga efectivo a la tabla de información y duplicaremos la cantidad con tokens. Por ejemplo\, $ 10 en efectivo equivalen a $ 20 en fichas.
URL:https://durhamcentralpark.org/upcoming-event/durham-farmers-market-8/2026-03-07/
LOCATION:Durham Central Park\, 501 Foster Street\, Durham\, NC\, 27701\, United States
CATEGORIES:Farmers' Market,Featured Events
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://durhamcentralpark.org/content/uploads/HuthPhoto-KAH_6070.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Durham Farmers' Market":MAILTO:info@durhamfarmersmarket.com
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260307T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260307T180000
DTSTAMP:20260306T165853
CREATED:20260303T210417Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260303T210417Z
UID:13273-1772892000-1772906400@durhamcentralpark.org
SUMMARY:Holi - the Festival of Colors
DESCRIPTION:Get ready to celebrate Holi – the Festival of Colors with Viceroy at Durham Central Park!\n\nJoin us on Saturday\, March 7th from 2-6pm for an afternoon of color\, music\, food\, and community. This free\, family-friendly event is open to all ages — come dance to a live DJ\, enjoy delicious food and drinks available for purchase\, and take part in the joyful tradition of throwing colors together.\nWe’ll have color powder available to buy for the celebration\, so please do not bring outside colors to the event. Whether you’re celebrating Holi for the first time or continuing a beloved tradition\, everyone is welcome to come experience the fun\, energy\, and togetherness of this vibrant festival!
URL:https://durhamcentralpark.org/upcoming-event/holi-the-festival-of-colors/
LOCATION:Durham Central Park\, 501 Foster Street\, Durham\, NC\, 27701\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://durhamcentralpark.org/content/uploads/Holi-Flyers-jpg.jpeg
ORGANIZER;CN="Viceroy":MAILTO:Bj@ViceroyDurham.com
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260308T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260308T153000
DTSTAMP:20260306T165853
CREATED:20260303T205750Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260303T205750Z
UID:13270-1772971200-1772983800@durhamcentralpark.org
SUMMARY:Communities Over Corporate Profits: How We Win
DESCRIPTION:Are you worried about the effects of climate change on our state? Concerned about the effect AI data centers may have on your bills or the impact of new pipelines on your air and water? Wish that communities and justice were being prioritized over a corporate bottom line? Join us to celebrate the wins that are happening and learn directly from community leaders who are advancing renewable energy projects\, pushing back on pipelines and data centers\, supporting education and labor rights and creating sustainable food systems and climate resilience. This is your chance to meet with organizations working towards progress in our state and to find out how you can fight for the land\, water and people of North Carolina!\n\nThis is a kid-friendly event\, snacks and beverages provided\, art-build with Paperhand Puppet and music provided by Drummah and DJ Big Feels and featuring an opening Keynote with Mayor Mondale Robinson of Enfield\, NC.
URL:https://durhamcentralpark.org/upcoming-event/communities-over-corporate-profits-how-we-win/
LOCATION:Durham Central Park\, 501 Foster Street\, Durham\, NC\, 27701\, United States
END:VEVENT
